-- South Korea's Ruling Party Wins Five Out of Eight Seats in By-Elections
-- Bomi Lim
-- 2010-07-28T22:22:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-28/south-korea-s-ruling-party-wins-five-out-of-eight-seats-in-by-elections.html

          
          
             South Korea’s ruling Grand National
Party won five of eight seats being contested in by-elections
yesterday, cementing its majority in parliament.  
 President Lee Myung Bak’s Grand National Party will now
hold 172 seats in the 299-member unicameral National Assembly,
according to results of the elections posted on the National
Election Commission’s website. Three candidates from the main
opposition Democratic Party won, boosting the party’s seats in
parliament to 87.  
